WEBVTT

00:56.173 --> 00:58.968
FILING FOR LOVE

01:06.225 --> 01:08.018
How could you miss something
this mundane?

01:08.269 --> 01:10.229
Not even a rookie would do this.
Get a hold of yourself!

01:10.896 --> 01:12.940
Order within an organization
is built on rank.

01:18.779 --> 01:19.822
However...

01:21.865 --> 01:23.659
the true power game between these two

01:24.493 --> 01:25.995
goes much deeper

01:26.620 --> 01:27.663
and far more quietly.

01:37.256 --> 01:39.258
TECHNICAL HIGH SCHOOL

01:45.514 --> 01:47.141
Does a completely equal relationship

01:47.725 --> 01:48.809
even exist?

01:58.319 --> 02:01.280
When two or more come together,
a hierarchy forms.

02:04.575 --> 02:07.161
Even between friends and lovers

02:07.786 --> 02:09.622
an imbalance of power is
almost inevitable.

02:22.468 --> 02:23.552
And everyone

02:24.345 --> 02:26.805
desires to rise higher,
even if only a little.

02:28.474 --> 02:29.475
Good job, everyone.

02:29.558 --> 02:30.601
Sometimes

02:31.268 --> 02:32.978
at the risk of doing things
they shouldn't.

02:34.980 --> 02:36.732
Gosh, that tastes so sweet.

02:40.903 --> 02:41.945
What's that?

02:42.363 --> 02:43.405
- What's what?
- What is it?

02:45.157 --> 02:46.867
- Something's hovering outside.
- Where?

02:46.950 --> 02:47.951
You see something?

02:55.793 --> 02:57.252
You're quite photogenic

02:57.336 --> 02:58.337
Director Kang.

03:08.138 --> 03:09.181
Are you the police?

03:09.890 --> 03:10.891
No, I'm not.

03:13.102 --> 03:14.186
I'm...

03:49.471 --> 03:50.514
NOH KI-JUN

03:52.766 --> 03:54.476
I'm with the Audit Team
at the head office.

03:54.935 --> 03:57.062
Stop what you were doing
and follow me for a chat

03:58.105 --> 03:59.231
Director Kang.

04:02.484 --> 04:04.653
INTERVIEW ROOM
AUDIT IN PROGRESS

04:14.788 --> 04:18.667
I heard Haemu's Audit Team
can bring down birds in flight.

04:20.586 --> 04:22.129
I see you send your own birds now.

04:22.212 --> 04:23.881
And you're about to crash and burn.

04:24.131 --> 04:25.507
- Hey, you!
- It's Assistant Manager Noh

04:25.591 --> 04:26.592
from Audit Team One.

04:26.675 --> 04:28.761
How dare an assistant manager
harass a director?

04:29.344 --> 04:30.471
Do you think you're the police?

04:31.054 --> 04:32.181
The National Intelligence Service?

04:32.473 --> 04:34.349
This is illegal filming.

04:34.975 --> 04:38.687
I'll sue you and your whole team
for invasion of privacy.

04:42.107 --> 04:45.402
It's the least I can do to catch
a spy who's selling core tech

04:46.445 --> 04:47.488
to an overseas competitor.

04:48.697 --> 04:50.365
We have our own struggles, too.

04:50.657 --> 04:52.534
It's always the unethical ones
who are obsessed

04:53.660 --> 04:56.413
with privacy and personal rights.

04:59.374 --> 05:00.417
Hey, listen.

05:01.627 --> 05:02.961
Don't go too far.

05:03.754 --> 05:07.174
Even if I were an industrial spy,
this is just my first offense.

05:07.257 --> 05:09.176
So if I act remorseful

05:09.259 --> 05:11.470
I'll most likely be let off
on probation.

05:17.434 --> 05:18.519
Director Kang.

05:18.602 --> 05:20.187
He speaks pretty good Korean,
didn't he?

05:20.270 --> 05:21.730
Because he's an ethnic Korean
from China.

05:21.814 --> 05:23.232
You could say he's Korean.

05:24.358 --> 05:26.860
A North Korean.

05:32.616 --> 05:35.244
Turns out this company was
a source of funding for North Korea.

05:35.828 --> 05:37.663
It was disguised
as a foreign-currency operation

05:38.747 --> 05:40.541
but it was actually run
by North Korea.

05:43.126 --> 05:44.127
Oh, dear.

05:46.296 --> 05:48.632
If you're charged with espionage,
that means

05:50.551 --> 05:53.303
you're not an industrial spy anymore
but an actual spy.

05:54.429 --> 05:55.472
Probation?

05:57.599 --> 05:59.685
You'll most likely go to prison.

06:01.311 --> 06:02.396
Darn it.

06:10.737 --> 06:12.447
- Oh, no.
- Don't do that.

06:13.031 --> 06:14.366
Will you calm down?

06:14.449 --> 06:15.993
This is so infuriating!

06:16.368 --> 06:19.496
You punks. I said it wasn't me.
Why won't you believe me?

06:19.580 --> 06:21.957
- Calm down, sir. We got a tip-off...
- "Calm down"?

06:22.207 --> 06:24.668
- We got a tip-off.
- A tip-off? What tip-off?

06:24.793 --> 06:26.753
I'm being framed, okay?

06:27.212 --> 06:29.298
Something's always going on
at Team Three.

06:29.965 --> 06:31.258
What is it this time?

06:31.800 --> 06:34.303
Someone sent an anonymous note
to Team Three saying

06:34.386 --> 06:36.430
he hid the fact that he was married
and approached her.

06:36.513 --> 06:39.182
As proof, she said
he has a mole down there.

06:39.474 --> 06:40.809
- What?
- Down there.

06:40.893 --> 06:41.894
Right there.

06:45.731 --> 06:46.773
Haemu Group.

06:47.649 --> 06:49.860
The 7th largest business in Korea
and 9th in sales.

06:50.444 --> 06:52.237
The top-ranking department

06:52.321 --> 06:54.072
in this conglomerate
with 42 subsidiaries.

06:54.907 --> 06:56.283
Even the head office's Audit Team

06:56.700 --> 06:58.660
has a hierarchy of its own.

07:00.037 --> 07:01.830
Audit Team One and Two

07:01.914 --> 07:04.207
handle major cases
such as embezzlement

07:04.625 --> 07:08.086
malpractice, collusion,
and information leaks.

07:09.796 --> 07:10.839
Audit Team Three...

07:10.923 --> 07:13.050
I'm not in the mood for coffee!

07:13.175 --> 07:14.801
Okay, fine. Get your hands off me.

07:14.885 --> 07:16.053
- Hands off.
- Okay.

07:16.136 --> 07:17.429
I'll show you.

07:17.512 --> 07:18.972
- No, don't!
- No, don't!

07:21.058 --> 07:22.059
No!

07:22.142 --> 07:23.143
Don't!

07:23.560 --> 07:24.645
Shoot.

07:24.728 --> 07:26.855
- Look!
- Oh, come on...

07:27.272 --> 07:28.315
Look carefully.

07:28.815 --> 07:30.359
Do you see a mole?

07:30.442 --> 07:31.777
- Don't cover it.
- What's his issue?

07:32.235 --> 07:33.278
I'm innocent.

07:33.570 --> 07:35.864
This is what they do.

07:41.578 --> 07:45.499
EPISODE 1:
UP&amp;DOWN

08:18.198 --> 08:19.866
Hello, sir. Good morning.

08:20.033 --> 08:22.786
If it isn't Noh Ki-jun,
the gentleman.

08:23.328 --> 08:25.872
You're having
a handsome start to the day.

08:26.164 --> 08:27.249
Thank you.

08:27.332 --> 08:28.917
- Have a great day.
- You, too.

08:47.561 --> 08:49.021
SAFEGUARDING CORE TECHNOLOGY

08:49.104 --> 08:50.188
FROM INDUSTRIAL SPIES

08:50.272 --> 08:51.773
HAEMU'S AUDIT TEAM

08:52.357 --> 08:55.152
Auditing increases
and improves the value

08:55.235 --> 08:56.945
of the company's business execution.

08:59.072 --> 09:01.366
NOH KI-JUN AKA MR. SMILES,
ASSISTANT MANAGER, AUDIT TEAM 1

09:02.409 --> 09:03.660
Oh, wow.

09:05.787 --> 09:06.788
"Mr. Smiles"?

09:06.872 --> 09:08.248
We can't have those
in the Audit Team.

09:08.331 --> 09:10.333
I didn't come up with it, okay?

09:10.751 --> 09:12.586
What's wrong with it?
It gives me pride

09:12.669 --> 09:15.088
that my colleague is
the face of the Audit Team.

09:16.048 --> 09:18.967
To be honest, Team Three yesterday
was a huge embarrassment.

09:19.051 --> 09:20.886
They let a guy
drop his pants in the office.

09:20.969 --> 09:23.055
It was utter madness.

09:23.138 --> 09:24.306
I dreamed of it, even.

09:24.389 --> 09:26.224
That guy's thing.

09:26.892 --> 09:28.685
- Oh, the shudders.
- Get out of my head.

09:32.439 --> 09:34.691
- It's just gimbap.
- Sorry. My bad.

09:34.775 --> 09:36.234
- Sorry.
- Anyway...

09:36.318 --> 09:39.321
Why should we handle stuff like that?
It's not at all dignified.

09:39.404 --> 09:41.114
We must look into everything
we get a tip-off on.

09:41.198 --> 09:43.158
That's why we have Team Three.

09:43.241 --> 09:45.035
Team One and Two
do all the important stuff

09:45.118 --> 09:46.912
and Team Three
gets the trivial stuff.

09:47.287 --> 09:48.747
They go on stakeouts

09:48.830 --> 09:51.666
to see how long people smoke
and poop during work hours.

09:51.750 --> 09:53.627
Once I saw them go around
all the break rooms

09:53.710 --> 09:55.587
to count the coffee mix packets.

09:56.546 --> 09:57.756
That's so depressing.

09:58.215 --> 10:00.133
People think our Audit Team
is powerful enough

10:00.217 --> 10:01.593
to bring down birds from the sky.

10:01.676 --> 10:04.012
- Team Three...
- Not Team Three.

10:04.554 --> 10:06.389
They're more like poop-scoops.

10:07.349 --> 10:08.809
I like the ring of that. Poop-scoops.

10:11.228 --> 10:12.813
What if someone were to hear you?

10:13.438 --> 10:14.439
It's Executive Assistant Park.

10:22.239 --> 10:23.365
- Gosh.
- My word.

10:23.448 --> 10:25.742
Hello, Ms. Park.
Isn't it a lovely day?

10:27.786 --> 10:28.870
It is.

10:30.163 --> 10:31.915
We got to see her before work.

10:31.998 --> 10:33.792
I have a good feeling about today.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.378
I'll go ahead.
You guys finish breakfast.

10:36.670 --> 10:38.171
What? You're going already?

11:00.318 --> 11:01.903
What's my afternoon schedule?

11:02.654 --> 11:04.948
You have a meeting
with Haemu Media's executives.

11:13.999 --> 11:15.208
I like your tie.

11:21.423 --> 11:23.008
You have a good eye, sir.

12:00.003 --> 12:01.379
- Ki-jun.
- Hey.

12:17.103 --> 12:18.146
Ki-jun.

12:18.605 --> 12:20.774
Our team saw the PR clip,
and everyone's raving

12:20.857 --> 12:22.692
and wondering who you are.

12:23.276 --> 12:25.612
Really? They'll swoon
if they see me in person.

12:26.696 --> 12:28.782
What are you doing today after work?

12:29.199 --> 12:30.283
How about a drink?

12:30.367 --> 12:32.786
I heard a nice wine bar
opened nearby.

12:33.245 --> 12:35.330
- Where is it?
- It's called...

12:46.383 --> 12:48.134
I'll be in touch, okay?

12:48.218 --> 12:49.386
Wait, Ki-jun.

12:50.303 --> 12:51.888
14TH FLOOR
PLANNING TEAM, AUDIT TEAM

13:00.313 --> 13:01.398
What the heck?

13:08.571 --> 13:09.614
Ji-hye...

13:12.492 --> 13:14.869
That's way too passionate a greeting
after a long break.

13:16.288 --> 13:17.664
I missed you.

13:18.832 --> 13:20.417
Will you meet up
with that other girl later?

13:20.750 --> 13:21.793
Hang out with me.

13:24.170 --> 13:26.214
No, wait. What?

13:29.384 --> 13:30.510
Aren't you getting married?

13:31.886 --> 13:32.929
You called it off?

13:33.013 --> 13:34.014
Not exactly.

13:34.889 --> 13:36.224
I feel a bit down.

13:36.975 --> 13:40.478
The idea that I'll be stuck
with one guy for the rest of my life.

13:43.315 --> 13:44.399
How about

13:45.650 --> 13:48.528
we have a good time
just one last time?

13:55.410 --> 13:56.703
I'm not that kind of guy.

14:06.296 --> 14:09.049
It's natural to feel uneasy
before the wedding.

14:10.550 --> 14:11.801
I'll entertain you instead.

14:12.802 --> 14:14.304
With a hefty cash envelope.

14:14.929 --> 14:16.973
What the heck is that?

14:17.640 --> 14:19.142
How much will you gift me?

14:26.107 --> 14:27.108
Hey.

14:47.295 --> 14:49.672
- What are you doing?
- Hey, Mr. Noh.

14:49.923 --> 14:51.216
Look at that. It's in bloom.

14:51.633 --> 14:53.510
I wonder who's watering
and looking after it.

14:53.802 --> 14:56.471
It's doing so well
in this desolate place.

14:56.721 --> 14:58.723
Gosh, you're very sentimental.

14:58.807 --> 15:00.683
I'm sure you don't care.

15:00.767 --> 15:03.228
Because your life's in full bloom.

15:03.311 --> 15:05.188
Ms. Hong from HR just told me.

15:06.231 --> 15:08.525
You might get a special promotion
for catching Director Kang.

15:08.608 --> 15:09.651
Is that true?

15:11.152 --> 15:14.364
- I can't say.
- Wait a minute. I guess it's true.

15:14.948 --> 15:18.660
You were Director Kim's favorite
when he was Head of Audit.

15:20.912 --> 15:23.289
I trust you'll look out for me
later on.

15:23.373 --> 15:24.499
Don't forget that, okay?

15:25.375 --> 15:28.128
Guys, have you heard the news?

15:28.753 --> 15:29.754
What news?

15:29.838 --> 15:31.381
People are losing their minds
here and there.

15:31.464 --> 15:33.133
A really scary rumor is going around.

15:33.216 --> 15:34.759
It's code red right now.

15:34.843 --> 15:35.844
What's going on?

15:37.929 --> 15:38.930
Joo In-a

15:39.806 --> 15:40.849
is back.

15:43.017 --> 15:44.018
Isn't that Joo In-a?

15:44.102 --> 15:45.437
- For real?
- It really is her.

15:45.895 --> 15:47.147
HAEMU INTRANET
1 NEW MESSAGE FROM MR. KIM

15:48.106 --> 15:49.482
She must be back.

15:49.566 --> 15:50.692
NEW MESSAGE
NEW NOTIFICATION

15:50.775 --> 15:52.360
What's going on?

15:52.444 --> 15:53.570
YOU GOT A NEW MESSAGE

15:53.653 --> 15:54.654
She actually came back.

15:55.738 --> 15:57.490
- What's happening?
- What do you think?

15:58.908 --> 16:00.160
- Joo In-a's here.
- Joo's here.

16:00.243 --> 16:02.162
- We're done for.
- Is she back for good?

16:02.245 --> 16:03.705
- What a disaster.
- I'll be damned.

16:04.914 --> 16:06.374
I HATE GETTING CC-ED TO EMAILS

16:06.458 --> 16:07.459
WILL OVERSEAS BRANCHES SUFFER?

16:07.542 --> 16:08.585
ALL SITES ARE ON STANDBY

16:08.668 --> 16:09.711
HOW WILL THIS CHANGE THINGS?

16:09.794 --> 16:10.962
I WONDER IF THE EXECUTIVES ARE AFRAID

16:11.588 --> 16:12.839
You know, at work

16:13.214 --> 16:15.133
you must beware
of those with nicknames.

16:16.134 --> 16:19.262
People give nicknames
to badmouth freely.

16:20.930 --> 16:22.891
I bet Joo In-a has

16:23.850 --> 16:25.268
a dozen or so nicknames.

16:25.977 --> 16:28.396
"Joo In-Out" is a famous one.

16:28.897 --> 16:32.358
Get on her bad side and you're out.

16:32.942 --> 16:35.361
I thought that was funny.
"Joo-tergeist."

16:35.737 --> 16:38.907
She's like a poltergeist
that stays at work day and night.

16:39.824 --> 16:42.285
I heard she earned a new nickname

16:42.368 --> 16:44.537
- while working overseas.
- What's that?

16:44.871 --> 16:47.332
She fought a gang
over a business license.

16:49.834 --> 16:50.835
They called her

16:52.712 --> 16:53.796
"Joo-sniper."

16:55.215 --> 16:57.258
She actually fired a gun?

16:57.342 --> 16:58.468
I'm sure it's just a rumor.

16:58.551 --> 17:01.012
How could something like that
even become a rumor?

17:01.304 --> 17:02.847
What's most important is

17:04.182 --> 17:06.100
which division she'll join.

17:07.018 --> 17:08.061
Don't you think?

17:20.990 --> 17:21.991
JOO'S IN THE ELEVATOR

17:22.492 --> 17:26.079
KIM JIN-HEE FROM PLANNING:
JOO'S IN THE ELEVATOR

17:26.913 --> 17:28.039
She's in the elevator.

17:28.122 --> 17:29.165
Which floor did she press?

17:29.499 --> 17:30.875
JOO'S IN THE ELEVATOR

17:30.959 --> 17:33.836
WHICH FLOOR DID SHE PRESS?

17:36.965 --> 17:38.841
She's smashing the Close Door button.

17:38.925 --> 17:41.886
I think my heart
is getting smashed, too.

17:43.429 --> 17:44.597
Passed the fourth floor.

17:47.350 --> 17:48.351
Fifth floor.

17:48.851 --> 17:50.144
Passed the sixth floor!

17:53.439 --> 17:55.066
Where the heck is she going?

17:55.400 --> 17:56.651
Did HR post a notice?

17:56.734 --> 17:57.902
No, not yet.

17:57.986 --> 17:59.320
HR AND INFORMATION OFFICE

18:00.655 --> 18:02.615
HEAD OF HR, HAEMU GROUP
BOO SE-YOUNG

18:08.413 --> 18:10.623
WOULD YOU LIKE TO PROCEED?

18:10.707 --> 18:12.584
APPROVAL OF APPOINTMENT,
JOO IN-A, DEPARTMENT HEAD

18:12.667 --> 18:13.668
CANCEL

18:13.751 --> 18:14.752
APPROVE

18:17.422 --> 18:18.423
Ninth floor.

18:21.676 --> 18:22.719
Tenth floor.

18:22.802 --> 18:24.387
Why does she keep coming up?

18:25.138 --> 18:26.973
AS LONG AS
SHE DOESN'T GET OFF WITH ME

18:27.056 --> 18:28.975
JOO IN-A, PLEASE GET OFF
WHY'S THE ELEVATOR SO SLOW TODAY?

18:31.185 --> 18:32.186
PHEW, I'M GETTING OFF FIRST

18:32.270 --> 18:33.271
I'M SO JEALOUS

18:35.231 --> 18:36.441
PASSED 13TH FLOOR

18:36.524 --> 18:38.109
WILL SHE GET OFF HERE?

18:38.192 --> 18:39.402
14TH FLOOR...

19:08.181 --> 19:09.223
It's the 14th floor!

19:18.858 --> 19:20.151
Stay calm, everyone!

19:20.485 --> 19:23.029
The Planning Office is
on the 14th floor, too.

19:24.030 --> 19:25.239
PLANNING OFFICE

19:25.490 --> 19:26.491
Put everything away.

19:26.574 --> 19:29.285
Hey, get rid of all the dust.
Wipe every single speck.

19:29.369 --> 19:31.371
Dump all the documents
and scrap papers on your desk.

19:31.454 --> 19:34.791
And your coffees!
Drink it up and dump the cups.

20:00.233 --> 20:01.776
Is there a Kim Gyu-yeong?

20:05.822 --> 20:07.615
ONE-DAY COURIER

20:08.366 --> 20:09.492
What are you doing to me?

20:16.624 --> 20:17.625
It's nice to meet you all.

20:18.042 --> 20:20.294
I'm Joo In-a, the new Head of Audit.

20:28.052 --> 20:30.930
Come on, now.
Why the dull atmosphere?

20:31.305 --> 20:33.099
How about I sing a song
to lighten things up?

20:40.106 --> 20:42.608
Thank you for the warm welcome.

20:44.110 --> 20:45.111
Nice to meet you.

20:45.653 --> 20:47.238
Manager Kwon Myeong-jin.

20:47.321 --> 20:48.656
Yes. I'm pleased to meet you.

20:49.699 --> 20:51.325
You sound overly pleased. Relax.

20:51.409 --> 20:52.827
I will. Sorry.

20:52.910 --> 20:55.037
I'm Mun Gyeong-jin,
assistant team leader of Team One.

20:55.455 --> 20:56.789
You're an assistant team leader?

20:57.123 --> 20:59.542
You look young for that title.
I hope we get on well.

21:00.376 --> 21:02.211
I'm Kim Tae-hwan,
Leader of Audit Team Two.

21:02.295 --> 21:04.380
- I hope we can work well.
- I really hope so.

21:04.464 --> 21:05.590
Let's try to get along.

21:06.424 --> 21:08.801
Jeong Dong-min,
assistant team leader of Team Two.

21:09.135 --> 21:10.136
I hope we get along.

21:10.678 --> 21:12.930
I'm Ju Yeon-u,
senior associate of Team One.

21:13.848 --> 21:16.184
Which Ju clan
does your surname belong to?

21:16.559 --> 21:17.560
Well...

21:17.810 --> 21:18.811
Is it from the word "juice"?

21:19.187 --> 21:20.605
Yes, you're right.

21:22.315 --> 21:23.566
I hope we get along.

21:24.108 --> 21:25.735
Wait, she's pretty normal.

21:25.860 --> 21:28.029
There are too many groundless rumors.

21:28.362 --> 21:30.490
Right. We got scared for no reason.

21:32.325 --> 21:33.367
Hello.

21:33.451 --> 21:35.620
I'm Sung Doo-gi,
a senior associate on Team One.

21:35.703 --> 21:36.746
I hope we work well together!

21:36.913 --> 21:38.164
I love your energy.

21:38.414 --> 21:40.374
- Let's work well together.
- Thank you.

21:40.458 --> 21:42.084
I'm Assistant Manager Ahn Min-su
from the same team.

21:42.168 --> 21:43.294
I hope to impress you.

21:44.253 --> 21:45.797
I look forward
to your impressive work.

21:46.214 --> 21:47.256
Thank you.

21:50.760 --> 21:52.887
Hello, I'm Assistant Manager
Noh Ki-jun of Audit Team One.

21:55.932 --> 21:57.433
Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun.

22:13.616 --> 22:14.659
Shall we get to work?

22:23.709 --> 22:25.461
Excuse me, Ms. Joo?

22:25.878 --> 22:27.380
I'm sorry to bother you
when you just came in.

22:27.964 --> 22:29.841
No problem. Give that to me.

22:35.721 --> 22:37.723
It's a routine audit notification.

22:37.807 --> 22:40.434
I need to send it right away.
Please approve it for me.

22:40.852 --> 22:42.186
Haemu Industries.

22:42.436 --> 22:43.855
You've audited them
for five years in a row.

22:43.938 --> 22:44.939
Yes, that's right.

22:45.606 --> 22:49.193
I've been in charge since my transfer
here from Haemu Industries.

22:49.277 --> 22:51.445
You've been auditing
your former boss for five years.

22:51.529 --> 22:52.530
Yes.

22:54.615 --> 22:56.492
You can stop now.
It must be boring for both parties.

22:58.119 --> 22:59.704
Our new rule that is no one audits

22:59.787 --> 23:01.747
the same subsidiary
for more than two years.

23:01.831 --> 23:03.666
One year if you used to work there.

23:07.587 --> 23:11.090
I get what you're saying, Ms. Joo.

23:11.924 --> 23:14.552
I know better than anyone
how they do business.

23:15.136 --> 23:17.555
I also know
which areas are usually corrupt.

23:19.015 --> 23:20.892
How corrupt is that place
that you couldn't

23:21.309 --> 23:23.102
get to the bottom of it
for five years?

23:23.603 --> 23:24.812
Pardon?

23:27.982 --> 23:29.358
Well, Ms. Joo.

23:29.984 --> 23:31.527
- What I mean is...
- You laughed?

23:43.831 --> 23:45.374
I told you to stop going.

23:46.626 --> 23:48.169
That's all you have to do.

23:49.211 --> 23:50.796
Why do you talk back at every turn?

23:51.005 --> 23:54.050
Do you think I'm here to have
a lengthy discussion with you?

23:55.217 --> 23:57.637
If you know
about Haemu Industries that well

23:57.970 --> 23:59.722
why did you only do
a brief look-over every year?

24:00.222 --> 24:02.183
You haven't found anything
that led to disciplinary action.

24:03.267 --> 24:05.394
You worked there for over ten years.

24:05.478 --> 24:07.313
You just couldn't bear
to punish anyone.

24:07.396 --> 24:09.148
No, it's not that at all.

24:09.231 --> 24:12.652
Then did you collude with them
to hide a sweet slush fund somewhere?

24:13.027 --> 24:14.236
Shall I go digging myself?

24:14.445 --> 24:16.697
To see if you audited them
or did business with them?

24:16.781 --> 24:18.616
Why would you
suggest something so dreadful?

24:18.699 --> 24:19.742
If that's not it...

24:20.910 --> 24:22.912
You probably don't take me seriously.

24:24.121 --> 24:25.498
I apologize.

24:40.930 --> 24:42.223
Don't you have any work to do?

24:47.812 --> 24:51.565
I'll speak with each of you
in a one-on-one meeting.

24:51.649 --> 24:53.776
Come to the interview room
when I call your name.

25:01.909 --> 25:03.494
MUN GYEONG-JIN,
CALCULATE SEVERANCE PAY

25:03.577 --> 25:05.204
HOW MUCH TO OPEN
A FRIED CHICKEN STORE?

25:05.287 --> 25:08.290
SHOULD I QUIT?

25:08.374 --> 25:10.126
I WANT TO CRY

25:10.209 --> 25:12.712
INTERVIEW ROOM

25:23.139 --> 25:24.807
Manager Ha Jin-u of Team Two.

25:35.359 --> 25:37.028
It turned into Jurassic Park
in an instant.

25:38.946 --> 25:40.990
Hey, how can you work right now?

25:41.073 --> 25:43.492
Why not? She had a point.

25:44.577 --> 25:46.537
Do specially promoted people
have something in common?

25:46.620 --> 25:48.330
I heard she got promoted three times.

25:50.750 --> 25:53.085
You want to audit
Haemu Pharmaceuticals again?

25:54.086 --> 25:55.755
You're working on something,
aren't you?

25:56.130 --> 25:58.090
What is it? What are they up to?

25:59.675 --> 26:02.136
When I have them
right where I want them

26:03.387 --> 26:04.472
I'll tell you then.

26:05.264 --> 26:06.849
You special promotion jerks.

26:17.651 --> 26:19.487
Can someone get Mr. Ha
a cup of water?

26:19.779 --> 26:20.821
Yes, ma'am.

26:23.532 --> 26:25.034
- I'm useless.
- No, you're not.

26:36.253 --> 26:37.922
Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun
of Team One?

26:40.007 --> 26:41.050
Okay.

26:47.389 --> 26:49.391
Our meeting will only
last three minutes.

26:50.309 --> 26:52.770
Good. I'm all for efficient meetings.

26:54.396 --> 26:56.607
Let's see, Assistant Manager Noh.

26:57.900 --> 26:59.235
A pretty favorable evaluation.

26:59.318 --> 27:01.403
You've received top evaluations
ever since you joined Haemu.

27:02.029 --> 27:05.282
- I was lucky.
- So it was all luck.

27:07.868 --> 27:10.871
You've handled only the biggest cases
in each subsidiary.

27:11.789 --> 27:13.415
You closed a lot of big ones.

27:13.833 --> 27:14.875
Yes, my luck

27:15.584 --> 27:17.169
followed as I worked hard.

27:18.087 --> 27:20.840
Let's make a minor change
to your role, Mr. Noh.

27:21.841 --> 27:22.883
A special promotion?

27:23.592 --> 27:24.635
Already?

27:25.219 --> 27:27.513
It's not
personnel evaluation season yet.

27:27.596 --> 27:28.848
That doesn't matter.

27:28.931 --> 27:31.267
Well, if that's what you want,
I'll willingly accept...

27:31.350 --> 27:32.810
I'm sending you to Team Three.

27:33.644 --> 27:34.770
What? To Team Three?

27:34.854 --> 27:37.606
You'll transfer to Team Three
and take over the PM cases.

27:37.982 --> 27:40.151
- "PM" is our code for...
- Personal misconduct.

27:40.484 --> 27:43.070
P for personal and M for misconduct.

27:43.529 --> 27:44.822
They're mostly workplace affairs.

27:45.447 --> 27:47.116
You want me to handle
office scandals?

27:48.409 --> 27:49.410
Yes.

27:52.746 --> 27:54.915
Okay, then. That means

27:56.083 --> 27:57.084
today is your new day one.

28:04.466 --> 28:07.595
Ms. Joo, how could you send me
to Team Three to investigate affairs?

28:07.887 --> 28:09.013
I can't understand why.

28:09.889 --> 28:11.682
Why should I help you understand?

28:12.016 --> 28:13.434
I exercised my right
as your superior.

28:13.517 --> 28:15.769
Yes, that's true. But you admitted

28:15.853 --> 28:17.396
that I performed well every year.

28:19.398 --> 28:20.441
You did great.

28:23.235 --> 28:24.236
He's joining us?

28:24.904 --> 28:26.739
I was going to inform you
when things got underway.

28:26.822 --> 28:28.532
I'm working on something
with my team.

28:28.991 --> 28:31.702
It's an important audit
on one of our subsidiaries.

28:31.785 --> 28:32.953
Let me finish it.

28:33.037 --> 28:35.247
Put all the info on our cloud server.

28:35.331 --> 28:36.916
I'll take a look
and allocate someone else.

28:37.666 --> 28:40.377
It follows a complicated logic
and involves many executives.

28:40.461 --> 28:42.922
It requires a very subtle approach.

28:44.131 --> 28:45.257
The only one for the job?

28:48.010 --> 28:49.136
That would be me.

29:09.615 --> 29:10.866
Gosh, this is fun.

29:13.410 --> 29:15.412
Mr. Noh, are you that special?

29:15.621 --> 29:17.081
Do you have some kind of superpower?

29:17.164 --> 29:18.791
Can you fly or teleport?

29:18.874 --> 29:19.959
Can you do the palm blast?

29:20.834 --> 29:22.461
Who do you think you are

29:22.544 --> 29:24.797
that you would be the only person
who can do this particular job?

29:26.382 --> 29:27.466
No way.

29:27.883 --> 29:30.928
Do you actually believe
some employees are irreplaceable?

29:31.470 --> 29:33.389
Apple's doing just fine
after Steve Jobs died.

29:33.764 --> 29:35.599
Do you think
a project will collapse without you?

29:35.683 --> 29:36.809
Audit Team 1, of all teams?

29:38.602 --> 29:40.771
How could you be so utterly naive?

29:41.188 --> 29:42.606
Okay, let's say you were mistaken.

29:43.107 --> 29:46.318
How could you voice that to me?

29:46.986 --> 29:48.028
That's plain arrogance.

29:51.782 --> 29:53.200
I'll let you off today
for making me laugh.

29:53.450 --> 29:55.035
Don't go overtime next time.

29:58.372 --> 29:59.832
Give me a reason, at least.

30:01.542 --> 30:04.503
There must be a reason you want me
to handle affairs.

30:06.380 --> 30:07.423
It's because

30:07.756 --> 30:08.757
you are...

30:11.760 --> 30:13.220
the best one for the job.

30:21.645 --> 30:23.314
Hey, what happened?

30:23.814 --> 30:25.607
I thought she was
going to promote you.

30:25.691 --> 30:27.568
Forget the promotion.
This is more like a demotion.

30:28.444 --> 30:31.572
He's going to Team Three
to investigate affairs of all things.

30:32.072 --> 30:33.115
Still.

30:33.532 --> 30:35.200
They're all nice people.

30:35.701 --> 30:39.455
That's true.
Everyone on Team Three is nice.

30:40.331 --> 30:41.957
Do you need help with anything?

30:45.336 --> 30:47.546
- Do you need help?
- They seem nice.

30:48.005 --> 30:49.631
You'll do fine wherever you go.

30:55.179 --> 30:58.265
Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun,
the ace of the Audit Team.

30:58.891 --> 31:00.100
Welcome.

31:00.184 --> 31:02.144
How old are you, Mr. Noh?

31:02.227 --> 31:04.021
Still not married?
Or haven't been able to?

31:04.646 --> 31:06.357
The one man here
who gave up on any promotions.

31:06.648 --> 31:07.941
Team Leader Moo Kwang-il.

31:08.025 --> 31:09.985
I heard that people
are reluctant to marry these days.

31:10.944 --> 31:13.447
Consider that a welcome kit.

31:13.697 --> 31:14.740
Look inside.

31:15.074 --> 31:18.160
Bookkeeper Pyun Hae-young
who keeps the team going.

31:19.411 --> 31:20.829
Everything you need is in there.

31:21.497 --> 31:23.624
We usually only give you two pens

31:23.707 --> 31:25.501
but I added one more
out of pity for you.

31:25.834 --> 31:27.711
Once you run out of ink
and need a replacement

31:27.795 --> 31:30.839
you must sign the ledger
before getting a new pen.

31:30.964 --> 31:33.592
Why would you go to such lengths
at a company as big as Haemu?

31:33.675 --> 31:34.760
If you don't like it

31:35.803 --> 31:37.388
blame that fool over there.

31:37.971 --> 31:41.433
You're taking it too far
when all I did was take batteries.

31:41.517 --> 31:43.936
You took a whole pack.

31:44.019 --> 31:47.022
A pack of size AA and AAA each.

31:47.815 --> 31:50.150
The guy is always on the lookout
for things to steal

31:50.567 --> 31:51.693
Manager Cha Sung-tae.

31:51.944 --> 31:52.986
Darn it.

31:53.570 --> 31:54.696
Excuse me, Mr. Noh.

31:54.780 --> 31:56.949
Welcome to Team Three.

31:57.241 --> 31:58.951
If there's anything
you need help with

31:59.034 --> 32:00.661
you can come to me at any time.

32:00.744 --> 32:02.955
Senior Associate Baek Hyun-kyu,
who thinks he's a troubleshooter.

32:03.038 --> 32:04.581
He's called "White Blood Cell"
for some reason.

32:04.665 --> 32:07.584
Oh, and before you sit down,
let me adjust your chair for you.

32:18.345 --> 32:21.014
Right! Assistant Manager Yoon Da-yae
is a part of this team.

32:21.765 --> 32:23.183
An SNU graduate with a certified CPA.

32:23.267 --> 32:24.601
The one with crazy credentials!

32:26.520 --> 32:28.021
Hello, Ms. Yoon.

32:29.982 --> 32:31.483
Ms. Yoon has that Gen Z attitude.

32:32.109 --> 32:33.152
You know what Gen Z is, right?

32:34.945 --> 32:36.029
You can't talk to her.

32:41.410 --> 32:44.288
What in the world is nice
about this team?

32:46.165 --> 32:47.249
I can't believe it.

32:47.958 --> 32:49.126
- Stop it, Manager.
- I...

32:49.209 --> 32:50.502
- That's crazy.
- What did I do?

32:50.586 --> 32:51.587
I...

32:52.337 --> 32:54.298
I can't believe
I'm a part of this team!

32:55.048 --> 32:57.050
Even her parents can't talk to her.

32:57.134 --> 32:58.427
- Why did you take this?
- Quiet.

33:20.574 --> 33:22.159
Dinner's ready.

33:27.039 --> 33:28.707
Will he be late again?

33:32.252 --> 33:33.587
HUBBY

33:40.677 --> 33:43.305
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

33:43.388 --> 33:45.641
You will be charged after the beep.

33:51.813 --> 33:54.316
WIFEY

33:56.777 --> 33:57.778
Yes?

33:57.986 --> 33:59.238
Yes, I understand. Goodbye.

34:00.197 --> 34:02.032
- How did it go?
- I talked to them.

34:02.115 --> 34:04.034
- They'll meet the deadline.
- Yes!

34:04.117 --> 34:05.786
Nice job.

34:05.869 --> 34:07.412
You've become good
at pressing the vendors now.

34:07.496 --> 34:08.622
It's all thanks to my teacher.

34:10.082 --> 34:11.250
You're getting a call.

34:15.128 --> 34:16.171
Hey, honey. Yes?

34:17.339 --> 34:19.132
Did I forget to mention?
I have a team dinner tonight.

34:21.635 --> 34:23.345
You're having another team dinner?

34:23.428 --> 34:24.930
Yes, I'm sorry. I've been busy.

34:25.013 --> 34:28.433
Hello, ma'am.
It's Jeong Mi-young speaking.

34:29.351 --> 34:31.311
Yes, hello.

34:31.520 --> 34:33.355
It's been a while
since your husband went home early.

34:33.438 --> 34:35.065
We've been too busy
with the task force.

34:35.315 --> 34:38.110
I'll let him leave
as early as possible today.

34:39.945 --> 34:41.822
Hey, honey.
I'll be home early. I'm sorry.

34:42.406 --> 34:44.992
Okay, don't be too late.

34:45.450 --> 34:46.451
Bye.

34:49.538 --> 34:50.747
Jeez.

34:59.506 --> 35:02.509
Who does she think she is
to let my husband go early?

35:04.636 --> 35:05.721
Darn it.

35:07.889 --> 35:08.932
How dare she?

35:10.976 --> 35:12.144
Who does she think she is?

35:15.897 --> 35:16.898
Damn it.

35:19.234 --> 35:20.736
I've had enough.

35:25.866 --> 35:26.867
Mr. Noh.

35:27.326 --> 35:29.328
These four seats are
the tip-off lines.

35:29.411 --> 35:31.288
You'll get lots of calls

35:31.747 --> 35:32.914
so pick up and accept the reports.

35:36.251 --> 35:37.753
- Yes, okay.
- Okay.

35:48.513 --> 35:49.681
You've reached Audit Team One...

35:51.058 --> 35:52.434
No, Audit Team Three.

35:52.517 --> 35:53.560
Hello.

35:53.894 --> 35:55.854
I'm not sure
if I should be bringing this up

35:56.313 --> 35:58.398
but I'm calling
regarding my team leader.

36:00.150 --> 36:01.777
Yes, I see.

36:01.860 --> 36:03.945
Are you looking
to make an internal report?

36:04.196 --> 36:07.407
I mean, my team leader
keeps farting in the office.

36:07.658 --> 36:10.243
It's a bit too much
to hear it go off all day.

36:10.327 --> 36:12.371
It's the worst office environment!

36:12.454 --> 36:14.414
At least give us an air purifier.

36:15.248 --> 36:16.416
I see.

36:18.168 --> 36:19.586
So your team leader farts?

36:33.725 --> 36:34.851
You've reached Audit Team...

36:35.435 --> 36:38.563
You damn asshole!
What took you so long to pick up?

36:38.689 --> 36:41.316
Yet you get paid a fortune,
don't you, you punk?

36:41.400 --> 36:43.276
- ...Three.
- What Three?

36:43.360 --> 36:45.487
You'll only get a grip
when that business goes down!

36:45.570 --> 36:47.739
- Does your company know you do that?
- Sure.

36:49.032 --> 36:50.784
- What would you like to report?
- Report, my ass!

36:50.867 --> 36:52.327
I'll report your damn life!

36:52.411 --> 36:53.412
What's your name?

36:53.495 --> 36:55.747
I'll talk to your chairman
and tell him all about you!

36:55.831 --> 36:57.499
What the heck is your name?

36:57.582 --> 36:58.875
What's your name?

37:03.964 --> 37:05.549
What are these?

37:05.632 --> 37:07.300
Evidence of infidelity!

37:07.592 --> 37:11.012
I had to go through the trash can
to retrieve those.

37:11.221 --> 37:12.639
Yes, so what are...

37:21.398 --> 37:23.024
Where are you going?

37:51.136 --> 37:52.179
Jeez.

38:02.981 --> 38:05.108
Mr. Noh, are you okay?

38:05.484 --> 38:07.527
You looked pale as you ran in.

38:08.695 --> 38:10.447
Is there anyone to pat your back?

38:11.072 --> 38:13.366
If not, I can always come in
for a second.

38:24.294 --> 38:25.462
I'm all right.

38:28.089 --> 38:29.716
Are you sure?

38:30.300 --> 38:32.928
You can take a break
if it's too tough for you.

38:33.678 --> 38:36.306
Nothing beats being healthy.

38:48.193 --> 38:50.028
Let's do proper introductions.

38:50.987 --> 38:53.782
The Head of Audit, Joo In-a.

38:55.116 --> 38:56.576
The former Head of Audit

38:56.660 --> 38:58.537
and the current Director
of Strategic Planning, Kim Han-su.

38:59.412 --> 39:00.539
I've heard a lot about you.

39:01.581 --> 39:02.666
Congratulations on your promotion.

39:04.209 --> 39:05.752
Head of HR, Boo Se-young.

39:06.503 --> 39:07.796
It's been a while, In-a.

39:09.965 --> 39:12.884
We used to work in the same team.

39:13.510 --> 39:14.553
But of course

39:15.262 --> 39:16.555
I started before her.

39:17.222 --> 39:18.431
Hey, Se-young.

39:18.890 --> 39:20.559
You're looking great.

39:20.892 --> 39:22.185
Things must be swell in HR.

39:26.064 --> 39:28.567
You two seem rather close.

39:29.317 --> 39:30.360
That's nice.

39:30.569 --> 39:34.239
This recent appointment was
a genius move, I must say.

39:34.906 --> 39:38.285
We can call our audit teams the sword

39:38.368 --> 39:40.871
of the vice president
and the president.

39:41.913 --> 39:44.499
Someone like Ms. Joo
would be perfect for the job.

39:45.333 --> 39:47.043
Oh, my. How did you know?

39:49.629 --> 39:50.881
I have a knack for swordsmanship.

39:54.217 --> 39:56.303
Ms. Joo has a witty sense of humor.

39:57.053 --> 39:58.597
You'll find it funny
once you get used to it.

40:01.099 --> 40:03.101
How does it feel breathing
the Seoul air again after so long?

40:03.184 --> 40:04.936
The air is the same everywhere.

40:06.021 --> 40:07.814
But the fine dust seems
to have worsened.

40:09.065 --> 40:10.108
So?

40:11.860 --> 40:14.070
Do you regret coming back?

40:22.454 --> 40:23.455
If I do

40:24.372 --> 40:25.790
do I have the option to go back?

40:44.225 --> 40:45.727
Look at the time.

40:46.186 --> 40:47.854
Why don't we grab some dinner...

40:47.938 --> 40:50.023
I have a lot of tasks
to figure out right now.

40:50.941 --> 40:51.983
Why don't we

40:52.776 --> 40:53.944
slice some steak next time?

40:54.027 --> 40:55.028
Yes, sure.

40:57.155 --> 40:58.198
Mr. Vice President.

40:58.698 --> 41:00.909
I'm eating with my parents tonight.

41:00.992 --> 41:02.202
My wife is probably there now.

41:02.953 --> 41:04.371
Goodness, Mr. Vice President.

41:04.955 --> 41:06.331
You're such a romantic.

41:08.083 --> 41:10.460
How's the president doing?

41:10.794 --> 41:12.504
He was discharged last week

41:12.879 --> 41:13.922
but we must keep an eye on him.

41:15.840 --> 41:18.385
I've been
checking his condition frequently.

42:15.942 --> 42:18.361
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected...

42:26.077 --> 42:28.288
- Your call cannot be connected...
- Darn it.

42:32.667 --> 42:34.169
WHY AREN'T YOU ANSWERING MY CALL?
PLEASE CALL ME

42:34.252 --> 42:35.503
Why aren't you picking up?

42:36.463 --> 42:38.548
Please call me.
Why aren't you answering my call?

42:38.631 --> 42:40.091
Give me a call.
Are you still having dinner?

42:40.175 --> 42:42.093
Honey, when are you coming home?

42:42.552 --> 42:43.636
When are you coming home?

42:48.767 --> 42:50.101
Damn it!

42:58.860 --> 43:00.111
All right, now.

43:00.779 --> 43:03.114
Our best duo, Mr. Son

43:03.698 --> 43:05.408
and Ms. Jeong.

43:08.453 --> 43:10.121
You know that
the launch of the new brand

43:10.205 --> 43:12.165
will decide the fate
of Haemu Foods, don't you?

43:12.248 --> 43:13.666
- Yes.
- I need you two

43:13.875 --> 43:15.460
to work together
and do your best as a team.

43:15.543 --> 43:17.295
- I'll do my best.
- So will I.

43:17.378 --> 43:18.880
- Can you really do it?
- I'll do my best!

43:18.963 --> 43:19.964
Now, cheers!

43:20.423 --> 43:21.841
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

43:21.925 --> 43:22.926
Let's do this!

43:23.009 --> 43:24.302
- Cheers.
- Good luck.

43:28.973 --> 43:30.016
That's nice.

43:30.642 --> 43:31.810
Did you drink yesterday, too?

43:31.893 --> 43:33.728
I really wanted
to keep myself from drinking tonight.

43:34.687 --> 43:36.106
This meat looks nice.

43:36.981 --> 43:38.900
It's beef we're talking about.

43:44.114 --> 43:46.991
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

43:47.075 --> 43:49.327
- Damn it.
- You will be charged after the beep.

43:52.539 --> 43:53.665
Darn it.

44:07.053 --> 44:08.388
The work is...

44:10.223 --> 44:11.266
Honey!

44:15.603 --> 44:16.688
I'm sorry.

44:21.442 --> 44:22.485
Darn it.

44:32.954 --> 44:33.955
Jeez.

44:35.582 --> 44:37.584
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected...

45:23.171 --> 45:24.672
What the... Open the door.

45:24.756 --> 45:26.925
Hey! Open the door right now!

45:27.008 --> 45:28.009
I'll kill you.

45:28.927 --> 45:31.054
Open the door! Hey!

45:31.137 --> 45:32.138
Honey.

45:35.767 --> 45:36.893
What are you doing?

46:04.671 --> 46:05.672
Heading home now?

46:10.593 --> 46:12.220
He's so out of it.

46:13.221 --> 46:15.390
He's become a different man
in just a day.

46:46.671 --> 46:48.298
- All right!
- All right!

46:48.381 --> 46:49.424
Great job.

46:50.758 --> 46:53.386
ANXIOUSLY WAITING FOR THE RESULT

46:53.469 --> 46:55.972
CHUNG SANG-HYEON
DROPS FROM 2 STARS TO 1 STAR

46:58.224 --> 46:59.851
The accuracy

46:59.934 --> 47:02.562
of your dance dropped quite a lot
in the verse...

47:04.105 --> 47:07.066
No rank lasts forever in this world.

47:09.110 --> 47:10.153
Hence

47:12.113 --> 47:13.740
the higher your ranking

47:14.449 --> 47:15.742
the more anxious you become.

47:42.393 --> 47:43.853
You're such an embarrassment.

47:44.103 --> 47:45.938
How did you know I was there?

47:46.647 --> 47:48.483
Did you snoop around
every restaurant I might be in?

47:48.816 --> 47:50.109
Why didn't you pick up your phone?

47:50.193 --> 47:51.736
I was having a team dinner!

47:54.322 --> 47:56.324
Can't you pick up your phone
while you eat?

47:56.783 --> 47:57.825
My phone?

47:59.494 --> 48:02.246
Right. You're always
cooped up at home.

48:02.330 --> 48:04.165
You wouldn't understand anything
about work life.

48:04.832 --> 48:07.001
You drive me crazy! Damn it.

48:15.468 --> 48:17.220
If you do not wish to remain weak...

48:19.347 --> 48:20.681
you must fight your way up.

48:46.165 --> 48:47.834
What do you mean...

48:47.917 --> 48:49.627
In the end, keeping your rank

48:51.295 --> 48:52.797
means survival.

48:54.799 --> 48:56.551
Don't lose heart.

48:59.011 --> 49:00.263
Leave no regrets.

49:00.805 --> 49:04.142
What? How did he not make it?

49:05.393 --> 49:07.687
Not only is he
a good singer and a good dancer

49:07.770 --> 49:09.397
but he's good-looking
and is good at everything!

49:09.897 --> 49:12.608
But he's a total ace.
How did he not make it?

49:13.359 --> 49:14.819
How come?

49:14.902 --> 49:16.237
Why?

49:58.613 --> 49:59.614
Excuse me, Mr. Noh.

50:01.616 --> 50:03.284
She has something to report
to the Audit Team.

50:04.202 --> 50:05.953
She's been waiting
since early morning.

50:11.334 --> 50:12.335
It looks like

50:13.753 --> 50:16.130
my husband is having an affair.

50:16.214 --> 50:17.298
Goodness.

50:18.257 --> 50:20.092
When my husband brought home

50:20.635 --> 50:24.514
perfume as a birthday gift,
I knew something was off.

50:24.597 --> 50:26.265
Wait, what about the perfume?

50:28.684 --> 50:31.479
No one buys a perfume
for a married man.

50:31.562 --> 50:32.813
What do you think that means?

50:33.356 --> 50:36.317
It means she wants to mark him
with that scent.

50:37.401 --> 50:40.696
She wants her man
to smell like something she picked.

50:41.239 --> 50:43.533
I've kept my eyes on my husband
since that day

50:43.616 --> 50:45.451
and he never leaves his phone.

50:45.910 --> 50:47.370
He even takes it into the shower.

50:47.453 --> 50:49.747
I read online that it definitely
means he's having an affair.

50:52.458 --> 50:54.168
And they're always working together.

50:54.669 --> 50:56.546
Not only do they
always go on business trips together

50:56.629 --> 50:58.089
but they even message
each other at night.

50:58.965 --> 51:00.716
Right. I have evidence, too.

51:13.312 --> 51:14.855
It's a strand of hair.

51:17.024 --> 51:18.776
I found it on my husband's shirt.

51:18.859 --> 51:21.445
It must belong to that woman.
I know it.

51:23.990 --> 51:25.950
Ma'am, we can't call this evidence...

51:26.033 --> 51:29.370
We'll investigate
and get back to you right away.

51:30.246 --> 51:31.289
Okay.

51:35.918 --> 51:36.919
What?

51:37.587 --> 51:39.839
We must go through the formalities
after receiving a report.

51:40.089 --> 51:43.009
We have to do the paperwork
and talk to the person in question.

51:43.634 --> 51:45.511
What is it? Go and check.

51:45.886 --> 51:46.929
Go, now.

51:48.764 --> 51:50.308
What am I supposed to check?

51:50.891 --> 51:52.852
Should I run a DNA test
on this hair or what?

51:55.354 --> 51:56.522
Come on.

52:03.571 --> 52:04.697
Anyway

52:05.072 --> 52:07.867
wasn't Mr. Son's wife
really frightening last night?

52:08.326 --> 52:10.328
She came all the way there
just because he didn't pick up.

52:11.037 --> 52:13.080
She apparently suspects something
is going on with Ms. Jeong.

52:13.539 --> 52:15.291
Ms. Jeong must feel so wronged.

52:15.374 --> 52:16.500
All she ever does is work.

52:17.001 --> 52:19.670
But I think I understand why.

52:19.962 --> 52:23.007
Couples only see each other
briefly at night.

52:23.090 --> 52:25.593
But you're with work colleagues
all day long

52:25.676 --> 52:27.511
and share more in common.

52:27.595 --> 52:29.597
And you talk to them much more.

52:30.181 --> 52:32.308
I would be concerned, too.

52:33.100 --> 52:34.352
I don't think I'd like that either.

52:34.560 --> 52:36.270
But there are limits.

52:36.354 --> 52:38.189
She was almost delusional.

52:39.690 --> 52:41.484
Gosh. What is this?

52:42.401 --> 52:43.653
She was infamous.

52:44.320 --> 52:46.781
FOOD BRAND PLANNING TEAM

52:46.864 --> 52:49.116
Director Kang will kill us
if we continue like this.

52:49.200 --> 52:51.327
They're exactly
what we agreed to during the meeting.

52:51.410 --> 52:54.455
- Stop making random changes.
- I don't see the point!

52:55.039 --> 52:57.416
Comparing them with domestic brands
isn't what we're doing.

52:57.708 --> 53:00.336
I kept saying that our focus is
on expanding into the global market!

53:00.419 --> 53:01.879
They're just colleagues.

53:02.380 --> 53:03.422
There isn't any affair.

53:03.673 --> 53:05.132
- What?
- Don't you remember?

53:08.135 --> 53:10.554
Let's analyze all corporations
making under a billion won.

53:11.097 --> 53:12.973
- We have to do this.
- Yes, ma'am.

53:13.099 --> 53:16.143
There are some discrepancies
in the business licenses, so...

53:16.227 --> 53:17.603
I see. Really?

53:21.649 --> 53:24.068
Mr. Noh. Come here. Hurry.

53:30.074 --> 53:31.492
- Are we all here?
- Yes.

53:32.118 --> 53:34.412
All right, then. We received

53:34.787 --> 53:37.748
a very important assignment
directly from the top.

53:37.832 --> 53:39.417
- Our team?
- From the top?

53:39.500 --> 53:41.043
Yes, so that means

53:41.293 --> 53:43.713
we must pause whatever we were doing
and handle this first.

53:44.004 --> 53:45.923
This may turn into a criminal case

53:46.215 --> 53:48.968
and blow up into a big story
if anyone outside hears about it.

53:49.218 --> 53:51.095
It must remain confidential

53:51.679 --> 53:54.140
as we resolve the matter
as quietly as possible.

53:54.223 --> 53:55.224
Do you understand?

53:56.517 --> 53:57.601
What is it?

53:57.977 --> 54:00.271
ON-SITE AUDIT TEAM SURVEY
HAEMU GROUP AUDIT TEAM 3

54:00.563 --> 54:01.564
So you're saying

54:01.981 --> 54:03.691
there's poppy here?

54:03.774 --> 54:05.860
Goodness, man.
I told you to be quiet.

54:07.278 --> 54:09.238
The security guard said
he found a poppy out back

54:09.321 --> 54:11.115
while cleaning up the flower bed.

54:11.198 --> 54:12.742
Not the field poppy
but the other kind.

54:13.159 --> 54:15.661
He thinks there may be more
in another place

54:15.745 --> 54:18.456
so we must handle this quietly
before it becomes trouble, okay?

54:20.416 --> 54:21.500
A pharmaceutical company

54:22.460 --> 54:23.502
with a poppy?

54:24.587 --> 54:26.255
Did you eat that flower?

54:26.756 --> 54:28.716
Don't go around eating random stuff
just because it's free.

54:28.799 --> 54:30.551
Goodness. Just keep looking.

54:39.310 --> 54:42.354
- Hello?
- It's Mr. Son's wife calling.

54:42.438 --> 54:44.857
Have you checked the hair?

54:44.940 --> 54:46.859
I'll e-mail you the result.

54:46.942 --> 54:49.028
I'm on a different assignment,
so I must hang up.

55:02.708 --> 55:03.751
Yes?

55:05.085 --> 55:07.546
You said you'd get back to me
after investigating.

55:08.214 --> 55:10.424
I was right, about Ms. Jeong, right?

55:13.052 --> 55:14.845
What will happen to them now?

55:15.638 --> 55:17.556
The company must
handle this strictly to...

55:17.640 --> 55:19.350
Please stop!

55:21.185 --> 55:23.103
Nothing is going on between them.

55:23.479 --> 55:25.856
They're only working hard
even as we speak!

55:25.940 --> 55:27.525
They're together again?

55:28.651 --> 55:30.694
- Did you see them?
- Ma'am.

55:31.737 --> 55:33.614
Please stop pestering me.

55:34.448 --> 55:35.950
You should go see the doctor.

55:36.033 --> 55:38.911
You know, you're being delusional!

55:53.300 --> 55:54.593
You got poop on yourself.

56:04.019 --> 56:05.062
Jeez.

56:14.613 --> 56:16.073
Is the rehearsal
in the conference room?

56:16.156 --> 56:18.075
Yes, I called everyone
and said we were on our way.

56:18.158 --> 56:19.159
- One second.
- Sure.

56:26.584 --> 56:27.626
Thank you.

56:30.754 --> 56:32.256
2. TARGET
SON MYUNG-SOO, JEONG MI-YOUNG

56:32.339 --> 56:33.924
3. METHOD
INTERVIEW, E-MAIL LOGS, CCTV

57:15.132 --> 57:16.550
I hope you bloom and blossom

57:17.843 --> 57:19.345
in this crappy office.

57:42.326 --> 57:44.244
Goodness, Mr. Noh.
Are you getting off now?

57:48.999 --> 57:50.960
I read your report
on Mr. Son Myung-soo's case.

57:52.044 --> 57:53.337
Are you sure that's it?

57:53.754 --> 57:55.547
Are you sure
they aren't having an affair?

57:56.548 --> 57:57.591
No.

57:58.342 --> 58:00.302
How can I be sure
of what's happening between them?

58:00.719 --> 58:02.221
There's no hard evidence

58:02.554 --> 58:04.431
so the circumstantial evidence
points to nothing.

58:07.518 --> 58:09.353
I like how you don't make up crap.

58:09.812 --> 58:13.023
But if this is only between them,
shouldn't you look more into it?

58:16.318 --> 58:17.736
- Hello.
- Hello.

58:17.820 --> 58:20.030
- Food Brand Planning Team?
- Yes.

58:20.114 --> 58:21.323
Are you working overtime?

58:21.407 --> 58:23.701
- Hello.
- Thanks for your hard work.

58:25.703 --> 58:28.497
But I don't see
Mr. Son and Ms. Jeong.

58:28.580 --> 58:30.332
They're getting ready
for the presentation.

58:30.416 --> 58:31.750
We're stepping out to eat dinner.

58:31.834 --> 58:33.293
Is that so?

58:33.752 --> 58:36.005
How do you know everyone in our team?

58:36.088 --> 58:38.215
You're just as they say,
Almighty Joo.

58:38.632 --> 58:41.010
- Almighty Joo?
- It means you have your eyes

58:41.093 --> 58:42.177
on everything and know everything.

58:42.720 --> 58:45.764
Goodness, people say that?
That's crazy.

58:45.848 --> 58:47.182
What? "Almighty Joo"?

58:48.058 --> 58:51.061
But I do know that the Brand Team
is doing something very important.

58:51.687 --> 58:53.856
Okay, since you're all working hard
until late in the night

58:53.939 --> 58:57.484
so I, Almighty Joo, will treat you
to something expensive and delicious!

58:57.568 --> 58:59.028
You are the Almighty Joo!

59:00.446 --> 59:02.906
I'll have it delivered here
for all of you to enjoy

59:02.990 --> 59:04.324
so you can go back upstairs.

59:04.408 --> 59:06.452
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

59:12.499 --> 59:13.542
Good luck.

59:13.625 --> 59:15.044
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

59:20.340 --> 59:22.009
Mr. Noh,
I need a new report from you.

59:22.217 --> 59:23.260
Sorry?

59:23.343 --> 59:26.221
I really must be Almighty Joo.
That's a great nickname.

59:34.021 --> 59:35.606
Why don't we go over our moves again?

59:37.191 --> 59:38.192
Yes, Mr. Son.

59:43.655 --> 59:44.656
But...

59:50.662 --> 59:51.663
what moves do you mean?

59:58.128 --> 59:59.171
Something like this.

01:00:20.734 --> 01:00:23.112
What do you mean
you need a new report from me?

01:00:23.737 --> 01:00:25.030
You'll find out by tomorrow.

01:00:25.531 --> 01:00:27.783
No, maybe today.

01:01:01.483 --> 01:01:02.484
Darn it.

01:01:15.330 --> 01:01:16.373
Are you all right?

01:01:17.583 --> 01:01:18.750
What about you?

01:01:20.502 --> 01:01:21.545
What was that?

01:01:27.092 --> 01:01:28.177
Darn it.

01:01:42.649 --> 01:01:43.901
Mrs. Son...

01:01:58.415 --> 01:01:59.458
What did you say?

01:02:00.083 --> 01:02:01.126
Delusional?

01:02:01.793 --> 01:02:02.920
Damn it.

01:02:04.838 --> 01:02:06.840
Why are you only blaming me?

01:02:07.716 --> 01:02:10.552
I'm not the one who's crazy.
That asshole and bitch are!

01:02:15.349 --> 01:02:16.850
I'm going to kill them.

01:02:58.183 --> 01:03:01.103
FILING FOR LOVE

01:03:01.687 --> 01:03:04.439
GUEST APPEARANCE
BY PARK HA-SUN, KIM JONG-TAE

01:03:29.214 --> 01:03:30.757
Mr. Noh is the pride of our team!

01:03:31.717 --> 01:03:33.218
He says you're the pride.

01:03:33.302 --> 01:03:34.469
How brazen.

01:03:34.553 --> 01:03:36.096
If only everyone else were like you

01:03:36.179 --> 01:03:38.890
this world would've been
a much better place.

01:03:40.017 --> 01:03:41.310
You're a fool

01:03:43.103 --> 01:03:44.688
Do your next assignment right.

01:03:44.771 --> 01:03:46.940
It's Zone F in level four
of the basement parking lot.

01:03:48.025 --> 01:03:49.818
- We need to expose them.
- Expose?

01:03:49.901 --> 01:03:51.653
How am I going to do that?

01:03:51.737 --> 01:03:54.323
Morals? Do you think
you're a police officer or a judge?

01:03:54.656 --> 01:03:56.199
Do you hate her that much?

01:03:56.283 --> 01:03:57.826
Should I just quit?

01:03:57.909 --> 01:04:00.871
You should've talked to me
if you wanted to leave the Audit Team

01:04:01.079 --> 01:04:02.456
instead of talking behind my back.

01:04:17.179 --> 01:04:19.181
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
